  "prompt": "How can I change the \"Ok Google\" phrase to something else in a Nexus 6?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Google Assistant does not allow users to change the \"Ok Google\" activation phrase to something else. The ability to customize the wake word is a feature that users have been requesting but has not yet been implemented by Google for the Assistant.\n\nHowever, if you want to use Google Assistant, you still need to use the \"Ok Google\" phrase or activate it using the home button or an alternative method like a voice command set in your device settings.\n\nIf you're looking for a more customized experience, you can explore third-party voice assistant applications that may allow for changes in wake words, but these will not be integrated with Google Assistant.\n\nAlways check for updates to your device and the Google app, as features can evolve and change over time.",
